<span id="freeTextContainer5204734192560765103">The uber-proud and arrogant Dombey; the scheming Carker, poor Florence, the proud Edith, Cap&apos;n Cuttle and more; what I found was character and coincidence overload in this study of family relationships, child cruelty, arranged marriages and other areas impacted by the Industrial Revolution. It also felt like it really took a long time to get going, in my opinion... but still, an entertaining saga overall. 6 out of 12.<br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1618626496i/31191363._SX540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/></span>
